#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/perl_search_replace.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sometimes you need to quickly search and replace strings in a file or group of files. There are many ways to do this, but this method uses `perl`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/perl_search_replace.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "To search for and  replace a particular string across multiple files in a directory, the command would be:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/perl_search_replace.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -pi -w -e 's/search_for/replace_with/g;' ~/Dir_to_search/*.html\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/perl_search_replace.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "For a single file that might have multiple instances of the string, you can specify the file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/perl_search_replace.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -pi -w -e 's/search_for/replace_with/g;' /var/www/htdocs/bigfile.html\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/perl_search_replace.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "This command uses vi syntax for search and replace to find any occurrence of a string and replace it with another string across a single or multiple files of a particular type. Useful for replacing html/php link changes embedded in those types of files, and many other things.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/perl_search_replace.md:27
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/sed_search_replace.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Options Explained"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/perl_search_replace.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "|Option | Explanation                                                   |\n"
"|-------|---------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| -p     | places a loop around your script                              |\n"
"| -i     | edit file in place                                            |\n"
"| -w     | prints out warning messages in case something goes wrong      |\n"
"| -e     | allows a single line of code entered on the command line      |\n"
"| -s     | specifies search                                              |\n"
"| -g     | specifies to replace globally, in other words all occurrences |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/gemstones/perl_search_replace.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "A simple way to replace a string in either one or many files using `perl`.\n"
msgstr ""

